SELECT 'Episode 4: Ishaq, Mata Rantai Silsilah Tauhid', 'kisah-ishaq-04-mata-rantai-tauhid', 'id', 'kisah-ishaq', 4, 1, 'Kehadiran Ishaq menjadi bagian dari silsilah kenabian yang menjaga ajaran tauhid dari generasi ke generasi. Allah berfirman, "Maka ketika dia (Ibrahim) telah menjauhkan diri dari mereka dan dari apa yang mereka sembah selain Allah, Kami anugerahkan kepadanya Ishaq dan Ya''qub. Dan masing-masing Kami angkat menjadi nabi" (QS. Maryam: 49).

Ishaq disebut pula dalam wasiat tauhid yang diwariskan turun-temurun. Ketika Ya''qub hendak wafat, anak-anaknya berikrar, "Kami akan menyembah Tuhanmu dan Tuhan nenek moyangmu, yaitu Ibrahim, Isma''il, dan Ishaq, (yaitu) Tuhan Yang Maha Esa dan kami (hanya) berserah diri kepada-Nya" (QS. Al-Baqarah: 133).

Allah pun menegaskan bahwa Ishaq termasuk para nabi yang diberi petunjuk, "Dan Kami telah menganugerahkan Ishaq dan Ya''qub kepadanya. Kepada masing-masing telah Kami beri petunjuk; dan sebelum itu Kami telah memberi petunjuk kepada Nuh" (QS. Al-An''am: 84).

Hikmah: tauhid adalah warisan paling berharga yang diwariskan para nabi. Ishaq bukan sekadar penerus keturunan Ibrahim, melainkan penjaga ajaran mengesakan Allah — sebuah mata rantai yang menyambungkan generasi demi generasi dalam iman yang satu.', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 19 AND number = 49), NULL, datetime('now');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO stories (title, slug, lang, series_key, episode_number, category_id, body, ai_generated, qc_status, source_format, status, confidence_score, related_ayah_id, pdf_ebook_id, published_at)
SELECT 'Episode 4: Ishaq, a Link in the Chain of Tawhid', 'kisah-ishaq-04-mata-rantai-tauhid', 'en', 'kisah-ishaq', 4, 1, 'Ishaq''s presence became part of the prophetic line that preserved the teaching of tawhid from generation to generation. Allah said, "So when he (Ibrahim) had left them and those they worshipped other than Allah, We gave him Ishaq and Ya''qub, and each [of them] We made a prophet" (Qur''an 19:49).

Ishaq is also mentioned in the testament of tawhid handed down through the generations. When Ya''qub was about to die, his sons pledged, "We will worship your God and the God of your fathers, Ibrahim, Isma''il and Ishaq — one God. And we are Muslims [in submission] to Him" (2:133).

Allah affirmed that Ishaq was among the guided prophets, "And We gave to him Ishaq and Ya''qub — all [of them] We guided. And Noah, We guided before" (6:84).

Reflection: tawhid is the most precious inheritance the prophets passed on. Ishaq was not merely a continuation of Ibrahim''s line, but a guardian of the teaching of Allah''s oneness — a link joining generation to generation in one single faith.', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 19 AND number = 49), NULL, datetime('now');

